1. CNode boots.
2. switch.d starts.
3. switch.d loads local /ukama/configs/switch/policy.json.
4. CNode connects to backend.
5. Backend emits node.online(cnode).
6. site-controller receives node.online.
7. site-controller looks up site and node role in Registry.
8. site-controller probes CNode switch.d status.
9. If policy loaded:
      fetch full policy
      validate against Registry
      cache observed policy
      derive site state
10. If policy missing/invalid/unreachable:
      mark site degraded
      wait for health/retry/operator fix
11. Health starts flowing every 10 seconds.
12. If policy hash changes later:
      fetch/validate/cache again.
